                <div class=3D"question-container">
   =20
        <p><span class=3D"image-caption center">
                                    <span class=3D"zoomable-image"><span></=
span><img src=3D"https://ds055uzetaobb.cloudfront.net/brioche/uploads/b5ZUq=
e4ZBx-group.png?width=3D1200" alt=3D""></span>
                                </span></p>

<p>You are building a rainbow building from \(N\) cubic unit blocks.</p>

<p>First, you put together 3 cubes each to form a group of \(1\times 3\)  c=
olumns and discard the remaining cubes.</p>

<p>Then, you put together 5 columns each to form a group of \(3\times 5\) c=
ubic bases and discard the remaining columns, as before.</p>

<p>Finally, you stack 7 bases over one another to build the desired \(3\tim=
es 5\times 7\) cuboid structure, as shown above, and discard all the other =
bases, as usual.</p>

<p>If there are a total of 52 discarded cubes, and \(N\) is a multiple of 1=
1, what is the least possible value of \(N?\)</p>

   =20
</div>
           =20

            <div class=3D"solution-container hide">
                <br><br>
                The correct answer is: <strong>682</strong>
               =20
            </div>
